            <!-- Contents -->
            <noteGrp type="workDesc">
               <note type="description">A poetical work on the perfect human being (al-insān
                     al-kāmil), the supreme intellect, the guarded tablet, the materia prima, and
                     the universal body. One of IA’s earlier Maghribi works. See Angela Jaffray’s
                     introduction and translation, The Universal Tree and the Four Birds (Oxford,
                     2005).</note>
               <note type="structure"/>
               <note type="contentsNote"/>
            </noteGrp>
            <!-- Stemmatics -->
            <note type="stemmatics">OY cites 21 mss., of which three are historic mss. The best
                  are Shehit Ali 2813 (621H, written by Ayyūb b. Badr in the presence of IA) and
                  Veliyuddin 51 (c. 762H, copied from al-Ḥabashī’s original).</note>
